t1.text: So mixed farming, sheep and cropping, probably kills less animals than cropping without sheep. 1000 mice/ha on a 1000ha farm is 1 million mice per farm.

t2.text: During a mice plauge numbers can reach 1000+/ha. Enough that some farmers can't sow a crop without the seed being eaten before it can germinate. So the spread poisoned seed over whole farm, killing 90%+ of them. Grazing sheep after harvest consume the missed grain that mice eat.
